message.content:
Sally and of course Mrs Septimus, for surely
Mr Septimus stood in the same case as
myself? But was id so? I allowed myself
to entertain for a moment the idea, the
strange, the unwelcome, the almost
inconveniablle idea, that Ariadne's arrival
would be inopportune; and with the idea came
a somewhat vulgar impulse, with which I refused,
to watch Mr Septimus more closely, Mrs
Cairne too and Mr Gillett who would ...
